# What is Website Technology Fingerprinting?

Website Technology Fingerprinting is the process of identifying the technologies used to develop and host a website through publicly available information.
Without accessing restricted areas or exploiting vulnerabilities, investigators can often determine:

* Web Server
* Programming Language
* JavaScript Framework
* CSS Framework
* Content Management System (CMS)
* CDN (Content Delivery Network)
* SSL/TLS Configuration
* Security Headers
* Analytics Services
* Hosting Infrastructure

This information helps security professionals understand how a website is built and managed.

