# Challenges

During Website Technology Fingerprinting, investigators may encounter:

* Hidden technologies
* CDN masking server details
* Reverse proxies
* Minified JavaScript
* Dynamic frameworks
* Different results across tools

These challenges highlight the importance of cross-verification.


# Best Practices

* Use only publicly available information.
* Prefer passive reconnaissance techniques.
* Verify findings using multiple sources.
* Respect privacy and legal boundaries.
* Document observations accurately.
* Never assume one tool provides complete results.


